race.comment: RAZELLA (6) returns with sound NSW form and a fresh win at Taree last prep. We've seen horses with similar profiles shape up nicely in Saturday grade in recent times. Now under Jackie Stoetzer's care, she looks well placed to make an immediate impact. Expect her to be hard to hold out late. THE INEOS (13) resumes off three trials. He's still relatively lightly raced, drawn well, and has more upside than most in this field. CHAMPAGNE EFFORT (7) doesn't win often but is rarely far away and meets a modest line-up. She's a genuine hope. CASPER DE LUNE (2) scored last start and looks the best of the rest. Include in wider exotics.
